  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, Musealization was ranked second in the number of evaluations, but its quality was only slightly better than Preservation.",
    "It showed limited use of control groups and complex evaluations.",
    "However, its sample sizes were larger, averaging around 40 participants per study, and its evaluation purposes were more diverse, including Education/Engagement and Technology or System Application.",
    "The variability in purposes and larger sample size may be due to the context of these studies, involving iVR experiences for larger groups, which, in turn, complicates the execution of more complex evaluations.",
    "Finally, Education is the area of application with the highest number of evaluations, greater quality, larger sample size, and more diversity in evaluation purposes, prominently featuring Education/Engagement."
